						               													<description>In KaZock, players try to get as many carrots as possible with dice luck and tactical flair.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sometimes it is better to be satisfied with what you have achieved than to risk too much. The main thing is that in the end you have your nose in front and most of the carrots are collected.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn, you roll three dice. Depending on the result of the dice, one or two carrots can then be taken from the supply or stolen by an opponent. Unfortunately, if you are unlucky you have to give back some of your hard-collected carrots.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game it is recommended to not only keep an eye on your own carrot pile, but to also watch the collections of the other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the carrot supply in the middle of the table is used up and the player with the most carrots wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
